# Line-ending policy: LF everywhere, in the index AND the working tree.
#
# Why: the repo had drifted to per-file mixed endings (29 CRLF + 15 mixed
# files as of 2026-07-02), which made editors flip whole files and produced
# unreviewable diffs. `eol=lf` keeps checkouts byte-identical across
# platforms; every toolchain here (Biome lineEnding=lf, tsc, vitest, Node)
# is LF-native, including on Windows.
#
# The renormalization commit that accompanied this file rewrote those 44
# files once — use `git diff --ignore-cr-at-eol` when archaeology takes you
# across it.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit binaries (text=auto detects most of these; pinned so a stray
# NUL-free binary can never be normalized).
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.webp binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.eot binary
*.zip binary
*.gz binary
*.node binary
*.wasm binary
